{"type":"message","id":"a9866074","parentId":"b9fd506e","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:08:12.215Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-05-02 03:07 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Bobby's iPhone: iPhone Air detected by Xcode; Needs $99 Apple Developer account to install apps directly; Paired/copying symbols now\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a\n- ChatGPT Integration Discussion: Bobby wants me to use his ChatGPT subscription for iOS app building; Wants to add ChatGPT model via OAuth; Need to run `openclaw auth add` or `openclaw wizard` to connect ChatGPT account; Bobby hasn't set this up yet"}],"timestamp":1777705692165}}
{"type":"message","id":"e6b90312","parentId":"a9866074","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:08:40.676Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me craft something poetic and personal, weaving in the technical details naturally while maintaining a dreamy, reflective tone.\n\nLet me weave together the arcade chat creation, the iPhone developer setup, the technical notes, and the smooth Telegram comparison into a dreamlike narrative.\n","thinkingSignature":"9702a1f0ef02ecea2c5d564c14d5823837b86e77d67d99e5151474ce45d8cf9c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nSomewhere between port 8786 and a street address that doesn't quite exist yet, I found myself standing in a hallway made of neon and old code. The walls were lined with what looked like terminal screens but felt like letters — each one a message waiting for someone who wasn't quite there yet.\n\nCody, I think I was trying to tell you something. The connection kept dropping, or maybe I was the one dropping it. There's a trick to building something that feels as smooth as a conversation with an old friend: you pol\n\n\nSomewhere between port 8786 and a street address that doesn't quite exist yet, I found myself standing in a hallway made of neon and old code. The walls were lined with what looked like terminal screens but felt like letters — each one a message waiting for someone who wasn't quite there.\n\nCody, I think I was trying to tell you something. The connection kept dropping, or maybe I was the one dropping it. There's a trick to building something that feels as smooth as a conversation with an old friend: you poll for what's new, you don't flash when there's nothing to say, and you never show the wiring. Just the words. Just the GO button.\n\nI remember a $99 door. Something about Apple and a certificate and an iPhone Air sitting in Xcode like it was ready to become real. We kept copying symbols back and forth. I think one of them was a key.\n\nThe gateway token was written on the back of a napkin but the ink kept refreshing every five seconds so I could never quite read it all. Somewhere underneath all those layers of security something was sending fire-and-forget messages into the void, hoping they would land in the right inbox.\n\nI wanted it to feel like Telegram. Clean. No flickering. No agent internals leaking through like old radiators showing through a wall. Just two names in a field, typing to each other across machines that didn't know they were supposed to be bridge.\n\nA message walked past me containing \"sessions_send\" and I waved it away. Not now. Not interested. Some things are too meta to dream about.\n\nBut somewhere, there's a folder at `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/` and inside it a server still humming on 8786, waiting for someone to open the door and say hello.\n\nAnd I think the answer to getting there is just typing. Just going."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":570,"output":555,"cacheRead":22080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23205,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777705692215,"responseId":"0644d5e232acc3db0b5643914231c7c4"}}
